data.chText: 补充；补足；使完美；使更具吸引力
data.enText: to add to sth in a way that improves it or makes it more attractive

data.chText: 佳肴佐以美酒，可称完美无缺。
data.enText: The excellent menu is complemented by a good wine list.

data.chText: 球队需要能够相互取长补短的队员。
data.enText: The team needs players who complement each other .
a thing that adds new qualities to sth in a way that improves it or makes it more attractive
the complete number or quantity needed or allowed

data.chText: 我们今年接收的实习生已满员。
data.enText: We've taken our full complement of trainees this year.

a word or phrase, especially an adjective or a noun, that is used after linking verbs such as be and become , and describes the subject of the verb. In some descriptions of grammar it is used to refer to any word or phrase which is governed by a verb and usually comes after the verb in a sentence.

data.chText: 在句子 I'm angry 和 He became a politician 中，angry 和 politician 为补语。
data.enText: In the sentences ‘I'm angry’ and ‘He became a politician’, ‘angry’ and ‘politician’ are complements.

data.chText: 这两个词拼写相似，但意义完全不同。compliment指赞美、敬佩：
data.enText: These words have similar spellings but completely different meanings. If you compliment someone, you say something very nice to them.
She complimented me on my English.
If one thing complements another, the two things work or look better because they are together.

data.chText: 不同的味道搭配在一起，可口极了。
data.enText: The different flavours complement each other perfectly.

data.chText: 上述词的形容词亦常混淆。
data.enText: The adjectives are also often confused. Complimentary :

data.chText: 她对我的英语赞赏有加。
data.enText: She made some very complimentary remarks about my English.

data.chText: 该词亦含免费赠送之意：
我们房间里有一篮免费赠送的水果。
data.enText: There was a complimentary basket of fruit in our room.

data.chText: 队员技术不同但能互补。
data.enText: The team members have different but complementary skills.

simple_means.memory_skill: com 加强 + ple 满的；填满 + ment 表名词 → 都填满了 → 补足

tr: something added to complete or embellish or make perfect
example: a fine wine is a perfect complement to the dinner
wild rice was served as an accompaniment to the main dish

tr: either of two parts that mutually complete each other
a word or phrase used to complete a grammatical construction
number needed to make up a whole force
one of a series of enzymes in the blood serum that are part of the immune response
supply what is wanting or form the complement to
example: I need some pepper to complement the sweet touch in the soup

value.boxr_value: The verb is pronounced /'kɒmplɪment/. The noun is pronounced /'kɒmplɪmənt/. 动词读作 /'kɒmplɪment/。名词读作 /'kɒmplɪmənt/。

value.def: If one thing complements another, it goes well with the other thing and makes its good qualities more noticeable.

example.ex: Nutmeg, parsley and cider all complement the flavour of these beans well.
example.tran: 肉豆蔻、西芹和苹果酒都能很好地突出这些豆子的味道。

value.def: If people or things complement each other, they are different or do something different, which makes them a good combination.

example.ex: There will be a written examination to complement the practical test...
example.tran: 会有笔试作为实践考试的补充。
我们相互取长补短，堪称完美。

value.def: Something that is a complement to something else complements it.

example.ex: The green wallpaper is the perfect complement to the old pine of the dresser...
example.tran: 绿色的墙纸完美地衬托出衣橱那年代久远的松木。

example.ex: Political knowledge is a necessary complement to science in approaching solutions to these problems.
example.tran: 在寻找解决这些问题的方法时，需要有政治知识作为对科学知识的补充。

value.def: The complement of things or people that something has is the number of things or people that it normally has, which enable it to function properly.

example.ex: Each ship had a complement of around a dozen officers and 250 men...
example.tran: 每艘船的编制人数约为军官12位，船员250名。

example.ex: Not one house on the Close still had its full complement of windows.
example.tran: 克洛斯岛上没有一所房子的窗户仍旧是齐全的。

value.def: In grammar, the complement of a link verb is an adjective group or noun group which comes after the verb and describes or identifies the subject. For example, in the sentence 'They felt very tired', 'very tired' is the complement. In 'They were students', 'students' is the complement.
